float.comment: this value when added by hold_info->combat_slot_selection_weights->in_range_bias should be greater than hold_info->combat_slot_selection_weights->consistent_slot_bias so that a combat slot with a heavy armor target in range gets a priority that is higher than the priority of the combat slot that you occupy with no enemies in range.

list.name: sim_inventory_category_priority
list.comment: The inventoryCategoryPriority list is used by SimInventory to define pickup behaviour for categories of items. The inventoryCategoryPriority list is an ordered list from lowest priority to highest priority. Entities holding a priority category item can ONLY pick up a new priority category item if it is HIGHER priority. Entities CAN pick up higher priority items if they are holding a lower priority item. When a higher priority category item is picked up the lower priority item is passed to the squad owner and distributed to another child if possible. SimInventoryItemCategories have NO EFFECT on the logic of adding items to squads, the SimInventoryItemCategories ONLY effect adding items to entities.

float.name: skill_point_mission
float.comment: This is set to 0 because a cmap mission also gives skill points based on the rewards section of map pool entries, so we are just using that value.
